explicit

Interface Model

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CTMC, CTMDP, DTMC, LTS, MDP, MDPGeneric<Value>, ModelSimple, NondetModel, NondetModelSimple, STPG
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CTMCSimple, CTMDPSimple, DTMCAlteredDistributions, DTMCEmbeddedSimple, DTMCExplicit, DTMCFromMDPAndMDStrategy, DTMCFromMDPMemorylessAdversary, DTMCSimple, DTMCSparse, DTMCUniformisedSimple, DTMCView, LTSExplicit, LTSFromDA, MDPAdditionalChoices, MDPDroppedAllChoices, MDPDroppedChoicesCached, MDPEquiv, MDPExplicit, MDPFromDTMC, MDPSimple, MDPSparse, MDPView, ModelExplicit, ModelView, ParamModel, STPGAbstrSimple, STPGExplicit, SubNondetModel

    public interface Model
    Interface for (abstract) classes that provide (read-only) access to an explicit-state model.

      • findDeadlocks

        void findDeadlocks(boolean fix)
            throws PrismException
        Find all deadlock states and store this information in the model. If requested (if fix=true) and if needed (i.e. for DTMCs/CTMCs), fix deadlocks by adding self-loops in these states. The set of deadlocks (before any possible fixing) can be obtained from getDeadlockStates().
        Throws:
        PrismException - if the model is unable to fix deadlocks because it is non-mutable.
